<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-909-460  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 909 460.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computer Reseller News  Nov 20 1989 n342 p151(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Advanced Concepts profits from software programs.andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Shalvoy, Mary Lee.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Regional computer system distributor Advanced Concepts Inc hasturned the unfortunate loss of its primary vendor, Open Systems,into a profitable opportunity by capitalizing on its expertise inselling vertical-market software packages.andP;  The company hasstarted a program to take on the exclusive rights for the salesand marketing of a number of software packages from smallerdevelopers.andP;  Advanced Concepts, until Jun 1989 when Open Systemsdropped its distribution network in favor of direct sales toresellers, distributed Open Systems accounting software andrelated materials to a reseller base of 600, accounting for 60percent of Advanced Concepts' revenue base.andP;  The company not onlydistributed Open Systems products but modified the vendor'ssoftware and developed new packages of its own.andP;  Advanced Conceptsis now very focused in its vertical-market focus.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Advanced Concepts Inc. (marketing).andO;Topic:     Vertical MarketValue-Added ResellersMarketing StrategyDistributorsSoftware PackagesDealers and Agents.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>